In a major development, Pakistans Naval Chief visited a disputed area, sparking heightened security concerns in the region. Sources indicate that the visit forms part of strategic military oversight amid ongoing territorial tensions. Analysts warn that this move could impact maritime security and diplomatic relations between neighboring countries. 

The visit comes at a sensitive time, as regional powers closely monitor Pakistans military maneuvers in contested waters. CNN-News18 brings you live coverage, expert insights, and detailed updates on this high-profile visit.
